History of changes

Version 2.0.5

  - Fixed english translation. Thank to Tae Wong.
  - Now used WarpIN for application installation.
  - The source code now can be obtained from git repository
  hosted on Bitbucket: https://bitbucket.org/glassman/charmap

Version 2.0.4

   - Added a workaround for drawing fonts that have an abnormally
   large lMaxCharInc or lMaxBaselineExt. Thanks to Alex Taylor.

Version 2.0.3

   - Characters Map/2 is translated to German language. Thanks to
   Christian Hennecke.

Version 2.0.2

   - The selected font, size and codepage are restored after restart 
   of the program.
   - Characters Map/2 now use WarpSans font for dialogs if it is possible.
   - Characters Map/2 is now covered by the GPL.

Version 2.0.1

   - Problems with opening the message catalog at start of the
   program from other directory.

Version 2.0.0
 
   - Second public release.
